By Kevin Okunzuwa  Benin  – Former President, Nigerian Union of Journalists(NUJ), Chief George Izobo, has commiserated with the family of late Malam Wada Maida, ex-Managing Director of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). Izobo, who also retired from NAN as an Editor, described Maida’s death as shocking, in a telephone conversation with a NAN Correspondent in Benin on Tuesday. “I just read about the death of NAN board Chairman, Maida. This is sad and shocking to me,” he said. The former NUJ national president prayed God to rest the soul of late Maida and console his immediate family and NAN for the loss. Maida, who was the Chairman of the Board of Directors of NAN, died on Monday in Abuja, at the age of 70. The former Editor-in-Chief and later Managing Director of NAN, was one of the pioneer editors of the agency. He served as the agency’s Regional Editor in Kaduna, Political Editor and London Correspondent, among others. (NAN) Lagos -  A former Managing Director of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), Dr Nwabu Mgbemena, is dead. Mgbemena, 71, died of cancer on April 22 in New Jersey, U.S. His close associate Chief Tony Idigo confirmed the death on Sunday in a telephone interview with NAN. Mgbemena was one… April 24, 2016 In "News" UMUAHIA - Gov. Theodore Orji of Abia State has expressed shock over the death of the immediate past Managing Director of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), Mrs. Oluremi Oyo. Oyo, who retired from NAN in 2013, died at the age 61 in a London Hospital on Wednesday. In a… October 2, 2014 In "News" ABUJA - The Nigerian media community on Thursday mourned the death of Mrs Oluremi Oyo, the immediate past Managing Director of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), who died on Wednesday. Oyo, aged 61, died in the UK, where she was recuperating, after receiving treatment from an ailment. Reacting to… October 2, 2014 In "News"